column5: Three hard-working anglers landed less than 11 basses for two days in BOQ! Never fished that poor this year and wondering what's the result of the Quinte Tournament? If even pro fails to get the bite, maybe we do not suck that much.

Good to see some husband and wife teams doing so well.
When got skunk in the BOQ while it turned out awesome result for these pros, I realize even the unit: light year is too small to measure the gap from us to PRO. :wallbash:
We took a day trip to Quinte on Friday. Caught over 30 fish but only one 4lbr
It's just time on the water James.  Key is to use the days like you had on the B of Q to learn from and adjust.  Everyone one of those teams have had days like you, that's a guarantee.
